@node "INSTALL" "SN CallStats v1.1 - Installation Procedures"
@toc "MAIN"
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN CallStats v1.1 - Installation Procedures
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

 1  Run the included installation script either of the following
    two ways:

    a.  Type "Installer Install_CallStats" from the Shell.

    b.  Click on the "Install_CallStats" icon from Workbench.

 2  The installation script moves the required files to your specified
    location and creates an environment variable pointing to the directory
    above it.

 3  Add "{#4PFiles:CallStats/SN_CallStats %23 COUNT}" to your sys.welcome
    (or your _Begin/_End files if you're using SN LoginConfig).  This will
    also display the call statistics, so there's no need to run it again.

 4  Add "CS |{#4PFiles:CallStats/SN_CallStats %23}" to your bbsmenu (and add
    the option to your main menu) so users can view the call statistics at
    any time after logging on.

    Note that the above {'s in 3 &4 are actually control-Q commands and modify
    the paths to reflect your setup!

 5  Reload your bbstext/bbsmenu via CNet's Control Panel menu (option
    #3, "Text/menu reload  RAmiga-T" and you're all set!

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
