@node "PGP" "SN CallStats v1.1 - File Integrity"
@toc "MAIN"
┌────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN CallStats v1.1 - File Integrity
└────────────────────────────────────┘

I've included a PGP signature of the main file(s) for authenticity.  You
must have a copy of my PGP public key to test this, so I've included that
also.  However, if you received this archive second-hand, don't hesitate
to request my key via email or finger.

Testing for authenticity:

From the CLI, type "PGP [filename.sig] [filename]" and it'll check it!

If the file fails this check, delete the entire archive and get it
somewhere else.  No telling what someone has done to it.  If you can't
find it anywhere else, I will accept requests via email.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
